@page "/agent"
@attribute [Authorize]

@* Route wrapper (the standard DI-safe module-gating pattern). ModuleGuard renders the interactive AgentView —
   which injects the agent / guardrail / approval / AI-chat services — only when the Agent module is enabled
   (Features:agent:Enabled=true); otherwise it shows a clean "module disabled" notice. Because the view is only
   instantiated when enabled, a disabled module never triggers a missing-service DI error. *@
<ModuleGuard ModuleId="agent">
    <AgentView />
</ModuleGuard>
